<paragraph id="8BBC36C52866FFF1F7A0F9B1FE08B670" blockId="38.[151,1436,1518,1831]" box="[199,427,1590,1615]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Depository: FMNH.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36C52866FFF1F7A0F9DDFD8BB718" blockId="38.[151,1436,1518,1831]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
The specimen is a remarkably well-preserved fossil, so much that A.D. Warren (pers. comm.), who saw the specimen in July, 2015, thought it was a fake. According to Warren it exactly resembles the extant 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D462866FFF1F38EF9F9FEA0B685" authority="Hewitson" authorityName="Hewitson" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pierella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvina">
<emphasis id="B977EAD72866FFF1F38EF9F9FA3FB6A9" box="[1257,1436,1662,1687]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Pierella helvina</emphasis>
Hewitson
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C034D462866FFF1F677F925FE0EB685" box="[272,429,1698,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Nymphalidae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D462866FFF1F6D0F925FD86B685" box="[439,549,1698,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Satyrinae">Satyrinae</taxonomicName>
), which is distributed from 
<collectingCountry id="F31476552866FFF1F430F925FC69B685" box="[855,970,1698,1723]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F31476552866FFF1F48AF925FBE9B685" box="[1005,1098,1698,1723]" name="Ecuador" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
with 
<collectingCountry id="F31476552866FFF1F3EEF925FB54B685" box="[1161,1271,1698,1723]" name="Colombia" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Colombia</collectingCountry>
being the 
<typeStatus id="54B888672866FFF1F20BF924FA3FB685" box="[1388,1436,1699,1723]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">type</typeStatus>
locality, except for the reddish color of the extant species. However, the fossil has not yet been studied in detail. In view of the young age of the fossil it is of little interest for calibration of the molecular clock, except for the evolution within the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D462866FFF1F6AFF889FD82B719" box="[456,545,1806,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pierella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAD72866FFF1F6AFF889FD82B719" box="[456,545,1806,1831]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Pierella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
